05265nam a22007575i 9780823296866DE-B159720230103011142.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230103t20212000nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232968667 a10.1515/97808232968662doi  a(DE-B1597)575322  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aREL0150002bisacsh1 aDuminuco, Vincent, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Jesuit Ratio Studiorum of 1599 :b400th Anniversary Perspectives /cVincent Duminuco. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2021] 4c©2000  a1 online resource (308 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tIntroduction -- t1 The Experience of Ignatius Loyola: Background to Jesuit Education -- tResponse to Howard Gray, S.J. -- t2 The "Modus Parisiensis" -- tResponse to Gabriel Codina, S.J. -- t3 How the First Jesuits Became Involved in Education -- tResponse to John W. O'Malley, S.J. -- t4 Development of the Ratio Studiorum -- tResponse to John W. Padberg, S.J. -- t5 Women's Ways of Knowing and Learning: The Response of Mary Ward and Madeleine Sophie Barat to the Ratio Studiorum -- t6 From the 1599 Ratio Studiorum to the Present: A Humanistic Tradition? -- t7 A New Ratio for a New Millennium? -- tAppendix A: The Characteristics of Jesuit Education -- tAppendix B: Ignatian Pedagogy: A Practical Approach -- tContributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe guiding pedagogical document for Jesuit education worldwide was definitively set out in a 1599 tome entitled Ratio Atque Instituto Studiorum Societatis Jesu, "The Plan and Methodology of Jesuit Education." This plan has been praised by scholars from Francis Bacon in the seventeenth century to Harry Broudy and Paul Shore in our day. Some scholars and educators, upon learning of this tradition for the first time, have called it a "best-kept secret." And so it was timely that, at the dawn of the new millennium, an invitational 400th anniversary celebration of the Ratio Studiorum would be held at Fordham University in October of 1999. The fruit of the scholarly papers presented there make up the substance of this book. In addition, two key documents of the late-twentieth-century renewal of Jesuit education are included in the appendixes of this volume. Both The Characteristics of Jesuit Education (1986) and Ignatian Pedagogy: A Practical Approach (1993) have been out of print in English and are provided here in full.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh1 aAschenbrenner, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCodina, Gabriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeJulio, Rosemary A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuminuco, Vincent J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElias, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGo, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Malley, John W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPadberg, John W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPascoe, Louis B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311118960408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831107072980 cprintz978082322047240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329686640uhttps://